Tormented Genius: The Struggles of Vincent van Gogh
William Morrow and Company | 1967 | ISBN: N/A | English | 212 pages | PDF | 24.4 MB


Of all the artists caught up in the ferment of the last half of the nineteenth century, perhaps none is more widely known today than Vincent van Gogh. Certainly none endured such incredible suffering. In a compassionate biography, Alan Honour tells his dramatic story and gives the reader a startling and intimate picture of this tragic individual
